Chisa?

261
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:54,357
Are you really mad?

262
00:12:54,524 --> 00:12:56,025
SHOCHU

263
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:57,610
I'll drink it.

264
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:00,321
Thanks for the drink.

265
00:13:00,488 --> 00:13:02,573
He drank two liters.

266
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,825
That took some guts.

267
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:05,410
Impressive, Iori!

268
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:07,245
I'm back.

269
00:13:07,412 --> 00:13:08,454
You're late.

270
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:09,872
Did something happen?

271
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:12,667
Some guy was hitting on me.

272
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:14,377
Are you okay?

273
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:16,421
Yeah.

274
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:19,132
You promised earlier today, right?

275
00:13:19,298 --> 00:13:21,467
I already have plans.

276
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:24,178
It's okay. You're talking about those guys, right?

277
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,680
Come on.

278
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:28,599
MEN'S BEAUTY PAGEANT
REGISTRATION DEADLINE: 30 MINUTES LEFT

279
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,852
Aren't you going to enter the men's pageant?

280
00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:33,438
I'm letting the younger students
do it this year.

281
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,857
Did you want to see me compete?

282
00:13:36,024 --> 00:13:38,943
Yes! I do!
I'll cheer for you in the front row.

283
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:41,446
Well, if you insist...

284
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:44,157
I ran away while he was registering.

285
00:13:44,323 --> 00:13:45,950
Impressive, Azusa.

286
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:48,494
-Are you going to cheer for him?
-Of course not.

287
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,330
-That's terrible.
-I'm glad you're safe.

288
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,249
You're in time for our gathering.

289
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,168
That's right.

290
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,335
Gathering?

291
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,796
We're here, just like we promised!

292
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:00,840
RUGBY CLUB

293
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:04,552
Contain your excitement,
Iori and Kohei!

294
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:09,307
This drinking party is crazier than usual.

295
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:11,851
Oh, that's...

296
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:14,103
You guys...

297
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:16,939
You...

298
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,566
Cakey! Wait! Wait! Wait!

299
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:25,615
Why me? Go drink with the guys from the tennis club!

300
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:27,700
What did you say?

301
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:29,660
Why did I ask you out?

302
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:31,579
That's not what I mean...

303
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:33,081
She smells like alcohol.

304
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:36,584
It's because you're hot.

305
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:41,339
Just like the tennis club.
They're all hot. That's why I joined.

306
00:14:41,506 --> 00:14:44,092
I thought I'd be happy if I found a boyfriend.

307
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:47,220
Then I'd have the perfect college life I dreamed of!

308
00:14:47,929 --> 00:14:51,599
But... Tell me!

309
00:14:51,766 --> 00:14:54,769
Why do I always end up like this?

310
00:14:54,936 --> 00:14:57,939
-She's a drunk mess.
-All that makeup isn't helping.

311
00:14:58,106 --> 00:15:00,399
I'm trying really hard, right?

312
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,111
-I'm trying really hard!
-Yeah.

313
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:05,530
You were trying hard.
In a bad way.

314
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:08,533
I studied how to do makeup,

315
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:11,786
and dressed up in clothes I'm not used to.

316
00:15:11,953 --> 00:15:13,788
I tried so hard to fit in,

317
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:16,290
and did things I didn't want to.

318
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:19,001
Movies and shows didn't teach me that!

319
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,754
-Well...
-I bet.

320
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:27,051
Why does everyone make a fool out of me?

321
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:30,221
-Everyone?
-She's talking about the guys from Tinkerbell.

322
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:31,931
Well, dressed like that...

323
00:15:32,098 --> 00:15:34,308
With that much makeup,
they'd think she's weird.

324
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:37,103
Everyone said I was cute at first!

325
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,272
Everyone was laughing!

326
00:15:40,398 --> 00:15:41,816
You let it slip out.

327
00:15:41,983 --> 00:15:44,402
Did I hurt you?

328
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:47,155
Even I already knew that.

329
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:50,324
At first, I didn't mind being treated as a joke.

330
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:53,578
As long as I could be friends and have fun,
I was okay with it.

331
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,581
-Really?
-Then isn't this what you wanted?

332
00:15:56,747 --> 00:16:01,460
But at the drinking party after the pageant,
those guys told me...

333
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:05,173
"We've laughed enough.
You can go home now."

334
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:11,220
I shouldn't have tried so hard to change.

335
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:14,932
No matter what I do,
I'm always getting laughed at.

336
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:17,768
And they're the ones laughing at me.

337
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:21,189
-Cakey, You...
-What are you talking about?

338
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:26,986
There's no one who's always laughing,
or always getting laughed at.

339
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:28,487
But...

340
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,698
I'll show you something interesting.

341
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,745
IZU UNIVERSITY SPRING FESTIVAL
MEN'S BEAUTY PAGEANT

342
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:40,249
-Nice!
-Yeah!

343
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:45,421
You guys always mistake the male pageant
for a bodybuilding contest.

344
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:48,758
Look who's talking!

345
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:50,885
Up next!

346
00:16:51,052 --> 00:16:54,013
I'm Kudo, the captain of the tennis club.

347
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,890
Nice to meet you.

348
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,393
Can you say a few words about your club?

349
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,603
You're so casual.

350
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,480
Because I'm talking with a guy.

351
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:04,774
Kudo, you can do it!

352
00:17:04,941 --> 00:17:06,025
Captain!

353
00:17:06,192 --> 00:17:08,277
You're going to win this year too!

354
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:11,781
Of course!
I'm on a different level from the others!

355
00:17:11,948 --> 00:17:14,242
Next!

356
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:19,288
-A pretty boy!
-Why is he in a uniform?

357
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:21,249
Wasn't he with the naked idiots?

358
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:23,042
I'm Kohei Imamura from Peek-a-Boo.

359
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:26,295
It doesn't matter.
I'm going to win anyway.

360
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:28,005
A few words, please.

361
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:32,134
Azusa Hamaoka!

362
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:36,180
Please go out with me,
not Captain Kudo from Tinkerbell!

363
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:40,268
Imamura confessed his feelings!

364
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:42,228
He stands out.

365
00:17:42,395 --> 00:17:45,773
How dare he use my name without asking?

366
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:49,568
No. Choose me instead.

367
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:53,281
Captain Kudo also confessed his feelings!

368
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:00,288
Who is she going to choose?

369
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:05,209
Whoa, it's Captain Kudo!

370
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:08,004
Sorry things turned out like this.

371
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:11,215
People are all at different levels.

372
00:18:11,382 --> 00:18:14,927
I bet there's a good match out there somewhere
for you too.

373
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:18,180
A good match?

374
00:18:25,396 --> 00:18:28,441
Too bad! I'm a man!

375
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:31,152
Oh, really?

376
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:34,905
I never imagined I was a good match for Captain Kudo
from Tinkerbell!

377
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:36,240
That's great, Kitahara!

378
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:39,493
You guys are on the same level
when you're dressed up like a girl!

379
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:44,081
Iori Kitahara from Peek-a-Boo
is entering the male pageant!

380
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:47,001
They did it.

381
00:18:47,168 --> 00:18:48,919
Hey, hold on! I--

382
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:53,090
What should I do?
The captain confessed his feelings for me!

383
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:55,468
It hurts to lose,
but I'll step aside.

384
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:59,013
Captain, I hope you two have a long happy life together!

385
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,974
-Who are those guys?
-Kudo! What's going on?

386
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,768
No! This is--

387
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,811
Oh, right, captain.

388
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,772
We've laughed enough.

389
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,107
-You can go home now.
-You can go home now.

390
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,614
Pretty funny, right?

391
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:24,622
They did it!

392
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:34,507
Congratulations on the women's beauty pageant
and the male pageant!

393
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:38,636
Let's have a toast! A toast!

394
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:40,054
That's a washbowl.

395
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:43,015
You can't toast with that.

396
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:45,059
Hey.

397
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,895
I just want to--

398
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:50,272
How should I put this...

399
00:19:51,816 --> 00:19:52,942
What's this?

400
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:54,276
It's what it looks like.

401
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:56,737
Do you want a bigger bucket?

402
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:58,447
That's not what I mean. I--

403
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,491
Drinking is better with lots of people!

404
00:20:00,658 --> 00:20:02,410
Don't just stand there.
Sit down.

405
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:11,961
What? If you want to drink with me,
then you should just tell me.

406
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:13,838
That's not what we mean.

407
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,339
Your makeup is thick as oil.

408
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:16,924
Just drop it already!

409
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,636
What's this? It's too strong.

410
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:23,597
-Of course!
-You finished it?

411
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:25,975
We've been trained well!

412
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:28,394
-They're good freshmen.
-Right?

413
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:31,230
-Give them to us.
-In your dreams.

414
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:33,691
They were against it at the beginning.

415
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:36,026
I was surprised when they asked me too.

416
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:38,154
It turned out great in the end.

417
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,489
Especially for her.

418
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:41,949
OKONOMIYAKI

419
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:45,327
You were in the beauty pageant, right?
You're so cute!

420
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:46,704
Can I take your order?

421
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:50,458
We have a yakitori stall.
Want to hang out later?

422
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:51,625
No thanks.

423
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:54,253
Hey, we talked to her first!

424
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:56,505
Don't be so cold!

425
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:59,717
Just let the other two handle the stall.

426
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:01,218
Stop!

427
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:07,641
Do you have some business with her?

428
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:10,269
She looks unhappy.

429
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:12,062
Hey! Get lost!

430
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:14,273
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

431
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,859
Come on.
Those guys are useless.

432
00:21:17,026 --> 00:21:18,652
Hey! Get up, you guys!

433
00:21:18,819 --> 00:21:20,654
It's time for the award ceremony.

434
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:23,616
Congratulations on winning!

435
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:25,659
Thanks.

436
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:29,663
The audience liked your stage performance.

437
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:32,625
-What's wrong?
-She looks mad.

438
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,668
Well, that makes sense.

439
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:36,795
-What?
-Why?

440
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:41,634
Well, Chii-chan entered the pageant
just for Iori and the others.

441
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:46,180
But Iori and the others
worked hard for another girl.

442
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:48,682
Chii-chan gets bothered by guys

443
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:50,935
because she entered the pageant,

444
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:53,604
but no one helped her.

445
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:55,314
That'd make anyone mad.

446
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:56,899
Now that you mention it...

447
00:21:57,066 --> 00:21:59,568
I'd feel mad too.

448
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:03,113
Who do you want to share this happiness with?

449
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:06,200
Yes. Well...

450
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:08,577
I want to share it with my boyfriend,

451
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:11,163
who's passed out drunk over there.

452
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:15,501
Your boyfriend? Him?

453
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:17,211
He's a pervert!

454
00:22:17,378 --> 00:22:20,256
I see. She used Iori to repel other guys.

455
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:22,967
So now they're a couple?

456
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,386
Come on. Those two...

457
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:27,471
What are they going to do?

458
00:22:27,638 --> 00:22:31,892
Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!

459
00:22:32,393 --> 00:22:33,394
DEEP BLUE AL FINE
KAYA MIZUKI

460
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:35,688
Here's your mic, Kitahara.

461
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:39,942
Me, too...? All right, let's do this!

462
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:43,445
-Yeah, sing your heart out.
-You guys seem to be having fun.

463
00:22:45,114 --> 00:22:51,120
A fairytale whispers
In a fake world

464
00:22:51,287 --> 00:22:57,042
Hiding in the complete darkness

465
00:22:57,209 --> 00:23:03,007
I reach for the forbidden fruit
In my last days

466
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:09,305
Now I know the meaning of the song about hope

467
00:23:09,471 --> 00:23:14,560
A broken gear will never stop again

468
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:22,151
Even if I were to lose everything
I'd still want you to know

469
00:23:22,318 --> 00:23:28,240
Trapped in the sky so far away
I'm praying with ripped off wings

470
00:23:28,449 --> 00:23:34,204
Because we span together
The vows of areppegio

471
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:40,127
If life sparkles only to the beat
of the resonating stars

472
00:23:40,294 --> 00:23:43,130
I'll sacrifice everything

473
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:47,676
Till death do us apart

474
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:49,762
Cheers!

475
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:57,186
Thank you!

476
00:24:02,066 --> 00:24:03,901
I might just be imagining things.

477
00:24:04,068 --> 00:24:05,527
What? Kitahara?

478
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:07,988
Everyone's looking at me differently.

479
00:24:10,324 --> 00:24:13,911
What? Is something happening to me?
Am I going to die tomorrow?

480
00:24:14,078 --> 00:24:16,121
Tell me! What's going on?

481
00:24:16,146 --> 00:24:16,914
NEXT EPISODE
"TOO LATE"
